oc:kn_053caee7 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When processing documents, transcripts, and generating examples" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Enforce privacy constraints throughout the entire workflow, not just at output: redact customer names/contact info from examples, anonymize company names if requested, and flag any sensitive information detected during processing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Brand materials often contain real customer data from sales calls and documents; leaking PII in generated guidelines is a compliance risk." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_26822456 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assembling the final guideline document from the template" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never include empty placeholder sections. Omit sections with no data entirely rather than filling with stubs." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Empty placeholders signal incompleteness and confuse downstream agents or humans consuming the guidelines." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_65e73308 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When synthesizing brand attributes into guidelines" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Distinguish Voice (constant personality, values, 'We Are / We Are Not') from Tone (formality, energy, technical depth that flexes by context). Voice never changes; tone adapts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This separation lets content creators maintain brand consistency while adapting to different channels and audiences." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_708c84de a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When saving guidelines to .claude/brand-voice-guidelines.md" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The agent's working directory may not be the user's project root (especially in Cowork). Always resolve the save path relative to the user's working folder, not the current working directory." ;
    oc:hasRationale "In Cowork and other environments, plugins run from cache directories. Writing to the wrong path makes guidelines invisible to future sessions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_74743474 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting guideline generation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before generating, verify sources exist. If none available: check for a previous discovery report, check .claude/brand-voice.local.md for known material locations, or suggest running discover-brand first." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Guidelines without sources are hallucinations. Always ground in actual brand materials." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_80cb4d2f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When the working folder cannot be resolved" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If no working folder is set, skip file save and tell the user guidelines will only be available in this conversation. They can still use enforce-voice immediately within the session." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Failing silently or crashing on save is worse than clearly communicating the limitation while preserving functionality." .

oc:kn_a8c5265d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating open questions for ambiguous brand findings" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every open question MUST include an agent recommendation. Turn ambiguity into 'confirm or override' — never leave a dead end." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Recommendations let users quickly confirm or override rather than starting from scratch, keeping the workflow moving." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_aa526515 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating overall guideline confidence" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the weighted aggregate confidence formula: Voice Attributes 30%, Messaging Framework 25%, Tone Matrix 20%, Terminology 15%, Language Patterns 10%. Convert High=1.0, Medium=0.6, Low=0.3. Thresholds: 0.85-1.0=High, 0.60-0.84=Medium, <0.60=Low." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Weighted scoring provides a consistent, reproducible confidence metric that helps users know how much to trust the generated guidelines." .

oc:kn_d317cfb1 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When saving generated guidelines to disk" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When saving guidelines, check if a previous version exists. If so, archive it as brand-voice-guidelines-YYYY-MM-DD.md before writing the new version." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Archiving preserves history and prevents accidental data loss when re-running guideline generation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

